    <ul>
        <li>Provides financial security in retirement.</li>
        <li>Many pensions are tax-advantaged, meaning you can save on taxes.</li>
        <li>Potential employer contributions in workplace pensions.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="pension-contributions">
    <h2>Pension Contributions</h2>
    <p>
        It's important to regularly contribute to your pension throughout your working life. Contributions may come from your salary, your employer, and government incentives.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="pension-planning">
    <h2>Pension Planning</h2>
    <p>
        Proper planning is crucial to ensure you have enough income to support your lifestyle in retirement. Consider factors like your desired retirement age, lifestyle, and any other income sources.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="pension-faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>How much should I contribute to my pension?</strong> It depends on your income, retirement goals, and age. A financial advisor can help you determine the best amount.</li>
        <li><strong>When can I access my pension?</strong> This depends on the type of pension you have. Generally, pensions can be accessed from age 55, but this may vary.</li>
        <li><strong>What happens to my pension if I change jobs?</strong> You can usually transfer your workplace pension to your new employer's scheme or a personal pension.</li>
    </ul>
